VOver the years I have published research papers on nuclear structure and reactions; condensed matter physics (e.g., semiconductors, molecular solids, and tunneling in physical and biological systems); chemical physics (e.g., the electronic structure of large organic molecules and polymers); and surface science (e.g., electron and positron diffraction). I have served as editor of "Surface Science" for the past decade, and currently write both research articles and reviews on aspects of this topic, especially the structure and properties of semiconductor surfaces. Most recently I have been working on the design of distributed systems to generate hard copies of digital color documents and the applications of control and communication theory for color control, remote machine diagnostics and prognostics, job management across distributed digital document systems, and the organization and control of document production in print-shop-like environments. I also have performed a number of studies of the management of research, its economic value, and its role in innovation.Over the years I have published research papers on nuclear structure and reactions; condensed matter physics (e.g., semiconductors, molecular solids, and tunneling in physical and biological systems); chemical physics (e.g., the electronic structure of large organic molecules and polymers); and surface science (e.g., electron and positron diffraction). I have served as editor of "Surface Science" for the past decade, and currently write both research articles and reviews on aspects of this topic, especially the structure and properties of semiconductor surfaces. Most recently I have been working on the design of distributed systems to generate hard copies of digital color documents and the applications of control and communication theory for color control, remote machine diagnostics and prognostics, job management across distributed digital document systems, and the organization and control of document pro