VAs a marine geophysicist and earthquake seismologist, I am interested in the physical properties of the Earth's tectonic plates, the nature of convection in the upper mantle, and the processes that form new oceanic crust at mid-ocean ridges.  Using arrays of seismometers on the seafloor and on land, I study the seismic velocity structure and anisotropy of the lithosphere and asthenosphere as a means of revealing variations in temperature, composition and the flow pattern associated with convection and the aging of the plates.  In the oceans, I have concentrated particularly on mapping out variations in crustal thickness and the structure of the underlying mantle to try to understand the pattern of melt generation and migration that supplies the magma that forms new crust.  Current projects include a study of a transform fault system on the East Pacific Rise spreading center and a seismic tomography study of California and the adjacent Basin and Range province.As a marine geophysicist and earthquake seismologist, I am interested in the physical properties of the Earth's tectonic plates, the nature of convection in the upper mantle, and the processes that form new oceanic crust at mid-ocean ridges.  Using arrays of seismometers on the seafloor and on land, I study the seismic velocity structure and anisotropy of the lithosphere and asthenosphere as a means of revealing variations in temperature, composition and the flow pattern associated with convection and the aging of the plates.  In the oceans, I have concentrated particularly on mapping out variations in crustal thickness and the structure of the underlying mantle to try to understand the pattern of melt generation and migration that supplies the magma that forms new crust.  Current projects include a study of a transform fault system on the East Pacific Rise spreading center and a seismic tomography study of California and the adjacent Basin and Range province.As a marine geophysicist and earthquake seismologis