VMy research area is "synthetic organic chemistry" and in particular, "exploration of new synthetic reactions". For example: to let the dehydration-condensation reaction between two organic molecules proceed under neutral conditions, we eliminated H2O in [2H] and [O] whereas its conventionally accepted form was in [H] and [OH]. While Lewis acid-catalyzed reactions between carbonyl compounds and enolates were considered highly selective and practical, we attempted Lewis base-catalyzed reactions. This turned out to greatly broaden its application potential. Our conception of using stable 1-fluorosugar in glycosylation reaction cleared long outstanding problems such as its drastic reaction conditions. My other study interests involve: (i) the chemistry of TiCl4 and the onium salts of azzromatics; (ii) aldol reaction using Sn(Otf)2 as Lewis acid; (iii) asymmetric reaction using Sn(Otf)2-chiral diamine complex; and (iv) the total synthesis of natural products such as Taxol.My research area is "synthetic organic chemistry" and in particular, "exploration of new synthetic reactions". For example: to let the dehydration-condensation reaction between two organic molecules proceed under neutral conditions, we eliminated H2O in [2H] and [O] whereas its conventionally accepted form was in [H] and [OH]. While Lewis acid-catalyzed reactions between carbonyl compounds and enolates were considered highly selective and practical, we attempted Lewis base-catalyzed reactions. This turned out to greatly broaden its application potential. Our conception of using stable 1-fluorosugar in glycosylation reaction cleared long outstanding problems such as its drastic reaction conditions. My other study interests involve: (i) the chemistry of TiCl4 and the onium salts of azzromatics; (ii) aldol reaction using Sn(Otf)2 as Lewis acid; (iii) asymmetric reaction using Sn(Otf)2-chiral diamine complex; and (iv) the total synthesis of natural products such as Taxol.My research area is "synthetic orga