VI have worked in diverse areas of Engineering and Applied Science, generally concentrating on the phenomenon of Light.  My philosophy has been that if one takes a very fundamental approach toward solving practical problems, one is just as likely to stumble across a basic scientific truth as someone who cares only about pure science.  This has the additional benefit that the pragmatic problem might become solved as well.  Thus with the hopeful goal of making a practical impact, I have covered a broad variety of diverse research topics; nonlinear optics, laser-plasma interaction, infrared laser chemistry, photovoltaic energy conversion, strained-quantum-well lasers, and chemical modification of semiconductor surfaces. Currently my main interests are in quantum computing and quantum communication, spin-based electronics, optoelectronics, high speed optical communications including optical code division multiplexing, photonic crystals, nano-photonics in general including advanced optical lithography, and sub-wavelength plasmonic optics.I have worked in diverse areas of Engineering and Applied Science, generally concentrating on the phenomenon of Light.  My philosophy has been that if one takes a very fundamental approach toward solving practical problems, one is just as likely to stumble across a basic scientific truth as someone who cares only about pure science.  This has the additional benefit that the pragmatic problem might become solved as well.  Thus with the hopeful goal of making a practical impact, I have covered a broad variety of diverse research topics; nonlinear optics, laser-plasma interaction, infrared laser chemistry, photovoltaic energy conversion, strained-quantum-well lasers, and chemical modification of semiconductor surfaces. Currently my main interests are in quantum computing and quantum communication, spin-based electronics, optoelectronics, high speed optical communications including optical code division multiplexing, photonic crystals, nano-